A massive ornate fingerprint rendered in intricate mandala patterns, composed of thousands of tiny human silhouettes standing in curved lines, set against a rich saffron and deep green gradient background. The fingerprint spirals inward toward a central glowing lotus flower, while delicate threads extend outward from the pattern like a complex web connecting to geometric nodes at the edges. The style evokes traditional Indian textile art meets digital circuitry, with gold leaf accents highlighting the ridges of the fingerprint. Small birds fly away from the upper portion of the design, suggesting freedom versus containment. The overall mood balances beauty with subtle tension, celebrating collective identity while hinting at surveillance concerns.
